You are in a Kitchen.
You can see a woman.
You can go west.
You are in a small kitchen.  There is a woman here, sitting on a bench and weeping into her apron.
> x woman

> x woman
She has been crying, you can tell.  Other than that, she looks like a nice and attractive woman.
> speak to woman

> speak to woman
"Daisy Tunnelly, at your service," you say, hoping that she won't throw you back in the dungeon.

"Belinda Oswyn at yours and your family," she responds politely.

"I don't mean to intrude," you say, "but I was just arrested for trespassing on a washed out bridge as I was trying to get home to Bree.  I was caught in the river.  By any chance, Miss Oswyn, would you be able to help me get home?"

"Bree?" Miss Oswyn manages a shaky smile, "I was born in Bree!  Of course I will help you.  Would you be able to do something for me?  My sweetheart Gomlin Drudukr has been exiled into the mines for supposedly speaking against the Princess, even though the real reason is that she does not want a man like him in court, who agitates for equal rights for dwarves.  Could you bring him a note for me?  The mines are just on the other side of the forest, where you will pass by.  I cannot go because they are watching my every move.  But you, Miss Tunnelly, could pass by unseen."

You accept the note.  Miss Oswyn fits you into an old basket and lowers you out the kitchen window into the garden outside.

"Now run, run north," she whispers at you.  As you flee, you hear guards coming into the kitchen and shouting starts.  You hope she will be all right.

Being a Bree hobbit, not at all used to these dense forests, you are soon completely lost in the woods.

