You are in a Wooded area.
You can see an Entwife.
You can go north or east.
You are in a dark wood.  You have no idea where you are.  You can see an entwife.
> x entwife

> x entwife
Nothing out of the ordinary.
> speak to entwife

> speak to entwife
"Daisy Tunnelly, at your service," you call up to the entwife.

"Oom, Hoom," the Entwife says, slowly bending down to look at you.  She picks you up and straightens again.  "What is this?  Hoom?"

"I am a hobbit of Bree," you say nervously, "I have wandered in this forest for hours and I am completely lost.  Can you direct me to the meadow?"

"Let us not be hasty, little hobbit," the Entwife says ponderously.  "Why should I help you?  Oom?"

"I am trying to deliver a note from a cook, Belinda Oswyn, to an exiled man," you explain.  "I got swept away in the flood and I just want to go home to Bree."

"Ooom, hoom," says the Entwife dubiously.

"Maybe I could do something for you in return?" you plead.

"I am lonely, little hobbit.  I have searched for Ents far and wide and I am now tired.  If you find an Ent, signal to me where he is and I will go to him.  Oom Hoom."  The Entwife lowers you to the ground and directs you to the edge of the forest.

"Thank you, good Entwife," you call up to her.
> go exit

> go exit

