You hand Gomlin the note.  He nods politely and accepts the note which he stuffs in his pocket unconcernedly.
> speak to Gomlin

> speak to Gomlin
"This is a note from Belinda Oswyn," you say.  "Belinda?  No kidding?"  He lights your candle and reads in silence for a few seconds.  "I am most grateful to you for bringing this to me," he says finally, bowing formally, "You are a princess among hobbits.  Is there any way I can repay you?"
"Directions to Bree?" you suggest.
"I cannot direct you there," he answers, "But there is a tavern where you can ask for directions.  If you leave the cave back to the meadow, you can take the road east.  West will take you back to the castle."  He hands you a little knife  "I found this when I was mining in here.  I can't use it, it is too small.  But maybe you will find it useful?"
