You are in a Tavern.
You can see men.
You can go out.
It is a rather rough tavern, but nothing worse than a Friday night at the Dancing Bear in Bree.  It is packed with men drinking and talking and laughing.
> x men

> x men
A band of big, tall, rowdy men.
> speak to men

> speak to men
"Play something for us, hobbit!  Aren't you little halflings supposed to be great musicians?"  They laugh uproariously.
> play flute

> play flute
You play a rolicking tune on your reed flute.  The customers hoot and holler appreciatively.  After you finish, a hobbit pushes his way to the front.  It is Tom Brockhouse from Buckland!  "Daisy!" he exclaims, "What are you doing so far from home?"
> x Tom

> x Tom
It's Tom Brockhouse, your old neighbour from Bree!  His eyes are goggling at you like he has seen a ghost.
> speak to Tom

> speak to Tom
"Hullo, Mister Brockhouse," you say politely.

"Daisy Tunnelly, as I live and breath!" he puffs in surprise. "What are you doing so far from Bree?"

Over a pint at a private table, you regale him with your tale of being washed away, arrested, meeting the Entwife, and talking to Gomlin.

Tom hastily escorts you out of the tavern.  "It's not safe for you here," he says, "if you angered the Princess Haifalutin's knight and aided a renegade!  The roads have been washed out between here and Bree but I will take you as far as I can."

He helps you into his wagon and you trot away briskly.  He leaves you right where the road ends.  "Best of luck Daisy," he says, touches his hat, and hastens back to the tavern.

